#governance-principles.hc-feature.over-rel.padding.lite
  .hc-chunk.hc-customize-text-wrapper
    h3.hc-feature-title The 10 Principles of Storecoin’s Governance
    p.hc-feature-lead Storecoin’s Governance takes a system that has been vetted for hundreds of years – the U.S. Constitution – and removes most of the politics by replacing it with technology, while also ensuring censorship resistance, absence of collision, and decentralization of power.
    div.list
      div.item
        span 1
        = ' '
        | Any $STORE owner can participate in Governance by staking and becoming a dWorker - but they must vote
      div.item
        span 2
        = ' '
        | Only one vote per dWorker - no matter the size of their stake (there is no plutocracy) (there is no delegation)
      div.item
        span 3
        = ' '
        | Any issue on a ballot will reach finality in a democratic voting process of checks and balances
      div.item
        span 4
        = ' '
        | Change in possible through Governance but change is difficult as each dBranch chamber has different incentives
      div.item
        span 5
        = ' '
        | Governance enable changes to features, key leadership, and monetary policy - monetary policy is most sacred
      div.item
        span 6
        = ' '
        | Only the Judicial Branch can propose Monetary Policy changes for a vote by the dBranch (there is no Fed)
      div.item
        span 7
        = ' '
        | The Community has a path to create change - even when not having a vote in Governance (a democracy)
      div.item
        span 8
        = ' '
        | To secure the network when it's at Severe Threat Level, security-level fixes can be made outside of Governance
      div.item
        span 9
        = ' '
        | Hard folks can be decided by Governance but any hard fork outside of Governance will be agressively defended
      div.item
        span 10
        = ' '
        | Storecoin can operate forever using a 1% block reward endownment and +1,000-year Treasury Schedule
